	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Earthbound Zero on 27C256</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hey there community,<br /><br />I searched the web but couldn't find an answer to my problem. Maybe you guys can help me. I did some SNES-Repros in the past but I'm new to the NES <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />I'm about to build an Earthbound Zero for my collection. Is it possible to burn it on two 27C256's? The PRG and the CHR-File are 256kb in size.<br /><br />If it is burnable, how to connect the eprom to the PCB?<br /><br />I got this information from this site:<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">TKROM &amp; TSROM (mapper 4):<br />PRG socket:<br />Bend up pins 1, 2, 24, 30 and 31 (or cut tracks 2, 24, 30 and 31)<br />Solder pin 2 to hole 24 (A16)<br />Solder pin 24 to GND (OE)<br />Solder pin 30 to hole 1 (A17)<br />Solder pin 31 to hole 2 (A18)<br />CHR socket:<br />Bend up pins 1, 2, 22, 24, 30, 31 (or cut tracks 2, 22, 24 and 30)<br />Solder pin 2 to hole 24 (A16)<br />Solder pin 22 to hole 31 (CE or CHR /A13)<br />Solder pin 24 to hole 2 (OE or CHR /RD)<br />Solder pin 30 to hole 1 (A17)</div><br /><br />Well, a 27C256 has just 28 pins, so erm.. I don't have to mind the information about what to do with pins 30 and 31, right?<br /><br />Any help is highly appreciated <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>lidnariq</b> [ Sat Nov 03, 2012 12:55 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Earthbound Zero on 27C256</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The number at the end of the part is kilo<em>bits</em>, so a 27C256 → 32KiB. For 256KiB you'd need a 27c2001 or something equivalent.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


