	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Earthbound Zero on 27C256</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />27C256 is a 32KB chip. And the ROMS you slit aren't kb, they are KB. Bytes. You'd need 8x 256's for each program and characrer side. You need a 27C020 for *EACH* side. And there should be wiring sheet on the front page. You should be able to work on from there.<br /><br />ETA: Tokumaru has a point.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


